[ Indistinct Chatter ]

3
00:02:57,886 --> 00:03:00,430
I wish you wouldn't do that around me.
It's so filthy !

4
00:03:00,514 --> 00:03:04,017
- Don't give me a problem
about the cigarettes.
- It's such a filthy habit.

5
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:07,187
Oh, my God !
Look at this.

6
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:12,734
Oh, Jesus !
This is so appalling !

7
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:15,904
I can't believe it !

8
00:03:15,946 --> 00:03:18,407
I can't believe
they gave it to him.

9
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,623
Ah, this is pathetic !

10
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:28,917
Now he's a loser
with a Jaguar.

11
00:03:29,001 --> 00:03:31,920
Seriously, who did he have to blow
to get that thing ?

12
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:36,049
- Good morning, sir.
- Mr. Willis.

13
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:38,886
- It's really, uh,
- Mr. Trask !

14
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,888
quite a piece
of machinery.

15
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,724
- Good morning, Havemeyer.
- Morning to you, sir.

16
00:03:43,807 --> 00:03:45,893
- Bene !
- Bene ?

17
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,145
- Bene ! Fabulous !
- What's fabulous ?

18
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:50,439
That fine piece of steel
you have back there.

19
00:03:50,522 --> 00:03:52,566
Ah, you don't think
I deserve it.

20
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:57,112
No, sir. On the contrary.
I think it's great.

21
00:03:57,154 --> 00:04:01,658
Should the headmaster of Baird be seen
putt-putting around in some junker ?

22
00:04:01,742 --> 00:04:04,203
In fact, I think the
board of trustees have had...

23
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:07,581
their first, true stroke
of inspiration in some time.

24
00:04:07,623 --> 00:04:11,960
Thank you, Havemeyer.
I'll take that at face value.

25
00:04:12,044 --> 00:04:14,129
I'd expect
nothing less, sir.

26
00:04:14,213 --> 00:04:17,424
Have a good day.

27
00:04:19,009 --> 00:04:21,011
- Morning, Mrs. Hunsaker.
- Good morning.

28
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:24,598
What have we here,
Murderer's Row ?

29
00:04:30,479 --> 00:04:32,940
- What was that about ?
- Nothing. Just saying hello.

30
00:04:33,023 --> 00:04:36,485
I like to say hello
to Headmaster Trask.

31
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:39,780
Sugarbush. Lift tickets and
condo vouchers.

32
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:43,659
- I thought we were goin' to Stowe.
- Sugarbush is Stowe, Jimmy.

33
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:47,788
We're doing it right. Thanksgiving
in Vermont, Christmas in Switzerland --

34
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:50,040
-Christmas in Gstaad is gonna cost us --
-'Staad.

35
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:53,293
The "G" is silent.
'Staad. George ?

36
00:04:53,377 --> 00:04:54,920
- 'Staad.
- Trent ?

37
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,339
- 'Staad, man.
- So what about 'Staad ?

38
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,299
Fine. The "G" may be silent,

39
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:02,052
but it's gonna take at least
three grand to get there.

40
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:06,181
- I'll talk to my father.
- Better yet, have my father
talk to your father.

41
00:05:06,265 --> 00:05:08,976
Or my father
talk to your father.

42
00:05:10,853 --> 00:05:13,480
You goin' home
this weekend, Chas ?

43
00:05:13,564 --> 00:05:15,691
Uh, I don't know.

44
00:05:15,774 --> 00:05:18,443
You goin' home to fuckin' Idaho
for Thanksgiving ?

45
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:20,696
I'm from Oregon.

46
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:22,948
I meant fuckin' Oregon.

47
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:26,034
-Charlie, how do you feel about skiing ?
-[ Laughing ]

48
00:05:26,118 --> 00:05:30,747
You in the mood for
the white-bosomed slopes of Vermont ?

49
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:33,709
Got a deal going.
20% off for my friends.

50
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:36,753
My father set it up.
Christmas in Switzerland.

51
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:39,089
- 'Staad.
- Gstaad. Dropping the "G" is phony.

52
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:42,384
- You said everybody says 'Staad.
- Not if you've been there.

53
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,637
Easter in Bermuda,
then Kentucky Derby weekend.

54
00:05:45,721 --> 00:05:47,848
We could fit you in, kid.

55
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:51,768
Well, how much are
these white-bosomed slopes of Vermont ?

56
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:53,770
Twelve hundred !

57
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:58,025
Includes a nine-course,
champagne thanksgiving dinner.

58
00:05:58,108 --> 00:06:01,778
$1200 is a little rich
for my blood, Harry.

59
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,864
Well, how short
are you ?

60
00:06:03,906 --> 00:06:06,033
How short, Harry ?

61
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:09,786
So short it wouldn't be worth the
trouble of you and George to measure.

62
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:12,789
- But, thanks for askin', all right ?
- Mm-hmm.

63
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:17,336
- If you change your mind --
- What'd you do that for ?
You know he's on aid.

64
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:20,047
On major holidays, Willis, it's
customary for the lord of the manor...

65
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:23,383
- to offer drippings to the poor.
- You're so full of shit !

66
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:52,579
- Hi. Mrs. Rossi ?
- Yes ?

67
00:06:52,663 --> 00:06:56,625
I'm here about
the weekend job.

68
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,627
Come on in.

69
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:03,173
[ Children Chattering ]

70
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:06,260
Does he got pimples ?
He hates pimples.

71
00:07:06,301 --> 00:07:08,095
Francine, be quiet.

72
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,806
Pimples. Pimples.
Yeah.

73
00:07:10,889 --> 00:07:13,308
Shush !
I'm sorry.

74
00:07:13,392 --> 00:07:16,562
- The school gave me your name,
but I've forgotten it.
- It's Charlie Simms.

75
00:07:16,645 --> 00:07:18,814
- How are you, Charlie ?
- Fine, thanks.

76
00:07:18,897 --> 00:07:21,108
Right this way.

77
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:27,447
- You're available the whole weekend ?
- Uh, yeah.

78
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:29,616
- Not going home for Thanksgiving ?
- No.

79
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,578
[ Mrs. Rossi ]
Good.

80
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,747
They put him in a veteran's home,
but he hated it,

81
00:07:35,831 --> 00:07:38,333
so I told my dad
that we'd take him.

82
00:07:40,085 --> 00:07:43,297
Before you go in, do you mind
my telling you a few things ?

83
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:47,801
Don't "sir" him and don't ask him
too many questions.

84
00:07:47,885 --> 00:07:52,598
And if he staggers a little when
he gets up, don't pay any attention.

85
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:57,352
[ Sigh ] Charlie, I can tell you're
the right person for the job.

86
00:07:57,436 --> 00:08:01,356
and Uncle Frank's
gonna like you a lot too.

87
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,942
Uh, where you gonna be
this weekend ?

88
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:06,153
We're driving to Albany.

89
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:11,116
Donny, my husband,
has family there.

90
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:18,415
- Do you want Tommy in or out ?
- [ Man ] Leave him out !

91
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:23,003
He's chasin' that Calico ginch
from the track houses again !

92
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,678
Down deep, the man
is a lump of sugar.

93
00:08:52,199 --> 00:08:55,702
- Sir ?
- Don't call me sir !

94
00:08:55,786 --> 00:08:59,206
I-I'm sorry.
I mean mister, sir.

95
00:08:59,248 --> 00:09:03,085
Uh-oh, we got a moron here,
is that it ?

96
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:07,172
No, mister --
Uh, that is --

97
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:10,008
Uh, Lieutenant.
Yes, sir, Lieu--

98
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:12,302
Lieutenant Colonel.

99
00:09:12,386 --> 00:09:17,224
26 years on the line, nobody ever
busted me four grades before.

100
00:09:17,266 --> 00:09:19,726
Get in here,
you idiot !

101
00:09:25,941 --> 00:09:29,152
Come a little closer. I wanna get a
better look at ya.

102
00:09:36,743 --> 00:09:39,162
How's your skin, son ?

103
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:42,040
My skin, sir ?

104
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:45,419
- Oh, for Christ's sake.
- I'm sorry, I don--

105
00:09:45,502 --> 00:09:49,131
Just call me Frank.
Call me Mr. Slade.

106
00:09:49,214 --> 00:09:53,051
Call me Colonel, if you must.
Just don't call me sir.

107
00:09:53,093 --> 00:09:56,096
All right, Colonel.

108
00:09:58,056 --> 00:10:00,767
Simms, Charles.
A senior.

109
00:10:00,851 --> 00:10:04,313
- You on student aid, Simms ?
- Uh, yes, I am.

110
00:10:04,396 --> 00:10:08,025
For "student aid"
read "crook."

111
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:10,736
Your father peddles car telephones
at a 300% markup.

112
00:10:10,777 --> 00:10:14,323
Your mother works on heavy commission
in a camera store.

113
00:10:14,406 --> 00:10:17,284
Graduated to it
from espresso machines.

114
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:18,994
Hah-hah !

115
00:10:23,582 --> 00:10:27,252
What are you, dying of
some wasting disease ?

116
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:31,757
No, I'm right --
I'm right here.

117
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:35,469
I know exactly where
your body is.

118
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:39,473
What I'm lookin' for
is some indication of a brain.

119
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:42,518
Too much football
without a helmet ?

120
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:47,272
Hah ! Lyndon's line
on Gerry Ford.

121
00:10:47,314 --> 00:10:51,026
Deputy Debriefer,
Paris Peace Talks, '68.

122
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:55,155
Snagged the Silver Star
and a silver bar. Threw me into G-2.

123
00:10:55,239 --> 00:10:57,199
G-2 ?

124
00:10:57,282 --> 00:11:00,452
Intelligence,
of which you have none.

125
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,791
[ Yelling ]
Where you from ?

126
00:11:05,832 --> 00:11:09,086
Um, Gresham, Oregon,

127
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:11,088
s-- Colonel.

128
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:14,007
What does your daddy do
in Gresham, Oregon ?

129
00:11:14,091 --> 00:11:16,009
Hmm ? Count wood chips ?

130
00:11:17,594 --> 00:11:21,390
Uh, my stepfather and my mom
run a convenience store.

131
00:11:21,473 --> 00:11:26,395
- How convenient ! What time they open ?
- 5:00 A.M.

132
00:11:26,478 --> 00:11:28,814
- Close ?
- 1:00 A.M.

133
00:11:28,856 --> 00:11:30,983
Hard workers.

134
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,944
You got me all
misty-eyed !

135
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:40,742
So, what are you doin' here
in this sparrow-fart town ?

136
00:11:40,826 --> 00:11:42,953
I, l--
I attend Baird.

137
00:11:44,788 --> 00:11:47,624
Attend Baird !

138
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:50,335
I know you go
to the Baird school.

139
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:53,380
Point is,
how do you afford it,

140
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:58,135
even with the student aid and
the folks back home hustlin' corn nuts ?

141
00:11:58,218 --> 00:12:03,015
[ Sigh ] I won a, uh,
Young America merit scholarship.

142
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:05,559
Whoo-ah !

143
00:12:06,810 --> 00:12:10,814
§ Glory, glory
Hallelujah §

144
00:12:10,898 --> 00:12:14,902
§ Glory, glory
Hallelujah §

145
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:19,656
- [ Knocking ]
- Who's there ?

146
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:23,327
- [ Knocking ]
- That little piece of tail ?

147
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:27,331
Get her outta here !

148
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:29,583
[ Girl Giggling ]

149
00:12:35,964 --> 00:12:38,926
Yeah.

150
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:42,429
Can't believe
they're my blood.

151
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:50,437
I.Q. of sloths and
the manners of banshees.

152
00:12:50,521 --> 00:12:53,065
He's a mechanic,
she's a homemaker.

153
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:55,526
He knows as much about cars
as a beauty queen,

154
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:59,321
and she bakes cookies,
taste like wing nuts.

155
00:12:59,404 --> 00:13:02,950
As for the tots,
they're twits.

156
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:05,744
How's your skin, son ?
I like my aides to be presentable.

157
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:12,668
Well, I --
I've had a few zits.

158
00:13:12,751 --> 00:13:18,215
Um, but my roommate, he lent me
his Clinique because he's from --

159
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:20,467
"The History of My Skin,"
by Charles Simms.

160
00:13:22,261 --> 00:13:26,473
You patronizing me,
peewee ? Hmm ?

161
00:13:26,557 --> 00:13:29,685
You givin' me that old
prep school palaver ?

162
00:13:29,768 --> 00:13:32,521
Baird School !

163
00:13:32,604 --> 00:13:35,983
A bunch of runny-nosed snots
in tweed jackets...

164
00:13:36,066 --> 00:13:38,610
all studyin'
to be George Bush.

165
00:13:40,612 --> 00:13:42,531
Well...

166
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:45,909
I believe President Bush
went to Andover, Colonel.

167
00:13:48,704 --> 00:13:51,039
You sharpshootin' me, punk ?

168
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,501
Is that what you're doin' ?

169
00:13:54,585 --> 00:13:57,754
Don't you
sharpshoot me !

170
00:13:57,838 --> 00:14:00,299
You'll give me forty.

171
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,843
Then you're gonna give me
forty more.

172
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:06,305
Then you're gonna pull K.P.,
the grease pit !

173
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:10,642
I'll rub your nose
in enlisted men's crud...

174
00:14:10,726 --> 00:14:14,771
till you don't know which end is up !
You understand ?

175
00:14:14,855 --> 00:14:16,773
Yeah.

176
00:14:16,857 --> 00:14:20,277
- What do you want ?
- What do you mean, what do I want ?

177
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:23,530
What do you want here ?

178
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:26,992
I wa-want a job.

179
00:14:27,034 --> 00:14:28,869
A job !

180
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:31,121
Yeah, I want a job
so I can make, you know,

181
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:33,957
my plane fare home
for Christmas.

182
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:36,627
Oh.

183
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:40,506
God, you're touching !

184
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:53,435
[ Radio ]
§ ...from the banks §

185
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:56,897
§ Of the
mighty Mississippi §

186
00:14:56,939 --> 00:15:02,611
§ Workin'
the whole night through §

187
00:15:02,694 --> 00:15:05,697
§ Till the
riverboat gamblers §

188
00:15:05,739 --> 00:15:08,742
§ Stop to make a killin' §

189
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:12,162
§ Bring it on back to you §§

190
00:15:12,246 --> 00:15:14,706
Still here, poormouth ?

191
00:15:14,748 --> 00:15:16,625
Hmm ?

192
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:22,130
Convenience store...
my ass !

193
00:15:22,214 --> 00:15:26,343
Hustlin' jalapeno dips
to the appleseeds.

194
00:15:27,469 --> 00:15:29,471
Go on.

195
00:15:29,555 --> 00:15:31,431
Dismissed.

196
00:15:34,059 --> 00:15:36,061
Dismissed !

197
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:46,238
[ Radio ]
§ Evangeline §

198
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:49,658
§ Evangeline §

199
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:52,077
- [ Children Chattering ]
- [ Charlie ] Mrs. Rossi ?

200
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:55,914
Charlie, we're up here !
Come on up.

201
00:15:57,207 --> 00:15:59,418
- Uh, this is Donny.
- Hey, Charlie.

202
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:01,545
Hi.

203
00:16:01,628 --> 00:16:04,840
Uh, Mrs. Rossi,
I got the feelin' I screwed up.

204
00:16:04,923 --> 00:16:08,594
- Oh, you couldn't have.
- It was a bad interview.

205
00:16:08,635 --> 00:16:11,138
That was no interview, Charlie.
You're it.

206
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:14,308
You're the only one that showed up.
You have to take the job.

207
00:16:14,391 --> 00:16:19,021
He sleeps a lot. You can
watch television, call your girlfriend.

208
00:16:19,104 --> 00:16:21,023
I promise you,
an easy 300 bucks.

209
00:16:21,106 --> 00:16:25,027
[ Sigh ] I don't get
an easy feeling.

210
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:28,447
[ Sigh ]

211
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:31,700
His bark is worse
than his bite.

212
00:16:31,783 --> 00:16:35,120
He was a great soldier,
a real hero.

213
00:16:35,204 --> 00:16:38,290
The man grows on you !

214
00:16:38,373 --> 00:16:42,461
By Sunday night,
you'll be best friends.

215
00:16:42,503 --> 00:16:46,089
[ Sigh ]
Charlie, please.

216
00:16:46,173 --> 00:16:49,801
I want to get away for a few days,
and Uncle Frank won't come with us.

217
00:16:49,843 --> 00:16:53,430
Six months ago, he could
sometimes tell light from dark,

218
00:16:53,514 --> 00:16:55,807
but now there's nothing.

219
00:16:55,891 --> 00:17:00,646
I feel better having
someone else around just in case.

220
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,818
Please ?

221
00:17:09,947 --> 00:17:12,491
Okay, Mrs. Rossi.
Sure.

222
00:17:12,574 --> 00:17:16,662
- [ Sigh ] Thank you, Charlie.
- Come here, you.

223
00:17:24,878 --> 00:17:26,839
There you go.

224
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:29,842
[ George ]
Chas ! Chas, hold up !

225
00:17:31,009 --> 00:17:32,928
- How ya doin' ?
- I'm good.

226
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:35,013
That's great.

227
00:17:35,097 --> 00:17:37,349
This can't go out.
This is on reserve.

228
00:17:40,561 --> 00:17:42,688
Here's the thing.

229
00:17:42,771 --> 00:17:46,191
I need the book tonight...

230
00:17:46,233 --> 00:17:49,987
- for a Thanksgiving quiz with
big-shit Preston in the morning.
- Yeah, I know.

231
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,364
That's why he put it on reserve.
This is our only copy.

232
00:17:52,406 --> 00:17:55,158
Chas, I'm pullin'
an all-nighter.

233
00:17:55,242 --> 00:17:59,955
Without that book
I'm dead, okay ?

234
00:18:00,038 --> 00:18:03,292
If it's not back by 7:30,
it's gonna be my ass.

235
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:06,962
Oh, I promise.
I promise.

236
00:18:13,719 --> 00:18:16,221
- [ Whispering ] Got it ?
- Yeah.

237
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:33,488
Just a second.
I gotta lock up.

238
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:40,579
Okay.

239
00:18:40,662 --> 00:18:43,707
God, can you wait to get out
of this dump or what ?

240
00:18:49,087 --> 00:18:51,006
Where you guys
going skiing again ?

241
00:18:51,089 --> 00:18:54,218
- Sugarloaf or --
- It's bush, Chas, Sugarbush.

242
00:19:04,144 --> 00:19:07,105
That's my boys. [ Whistles ]
What are you doin' ?

243
00:19:07,189 --> 00:19:10,108
Keep your voice down !

244
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:12,444
I'll tell you about it
in the morning.

245
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:16,031
- Shh.
- Wha--

246
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:22,204
- Miss Hunsaker, have a nice day ?
- George, why all the noise ?

247
00:19:22,287 --> 00:19:25,249
[ Whispering ]
It's hunsaker ! Go ! Go !

248
00:19:25,332 --> 00:19:27,835
I was just
messin' around with Chas.

249
00:19:27,876 --> 00:19:29,920
- Good evening, Charles.
- Hi, Mrs. Hunsaker.

250
00:19:36,969 --> 00:19:38,971
- What was that ?
- I don't know, ma'am.

251
00:19:39,054 --> 00:19:42,432
- Who were those boys ?
What were they doing ?
- Oh, who knows ?

252
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:46,019
- Charles ?
- Um --

253
00:19:46,103 --> 00:19:49,857
- Did you make this scarf yourself ?
- No, George, I bought it.

254
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:52,693
- 'Cause it's a beauty. It really is.
- Thank you, George.

255
00:19:52,776 --> 00:19:55,487
In case I don't see you before
the Thanksgiving holidays,

256
00:19:55,571 --> 00:19:58,448
- why don't you give me
one of your big hugs ?
- Oh, George !

257
00:19:58,532 --> 00:20:00,492
- Please ? Come on.
- Good evening, boys.

258
00:20:00,576 --> 00:20:02,995
Good-bye,
Mrs. Hunsaker.

259
00:20:22,181 --> 00:20:27,019
[ Jimmy On Loudspeaker ]
Mr. Trask is our fearless leader,

260
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:31,815
a man of learning,
a voracious reader.

261
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:36,320
He could recite the "Iliad"
in ancient greek...

262
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:40,699
while fishing for trout
in a rippling creek.

263
00:20:40,782 --> 00:20:45,537
Endowed with wisdom,
of judgement sound,

264
00:20:45,579 --> 00:20:50,292
nevertheless about him
the questions abound.

265
00:20:51,418 --> 00:20:53,795
[ Hissing Sound ]

266
00:20:53,921 --> 00:20:59,343
How does Mr. Trask
make such wonderful deals ?

267
00:20:59,426 --> 00:21:03,514
Why did the trustees
buy him Jaguar wheels ?

268
00:21:03,597 --> 00:21:05,807
He wasn't conniving !

269
00:21:05,891 --> 00:21:09,144
He wasn't crass !

270
00:21:09,228 --> 00:21:12,606
He merely
puckered his lips...

271
00:21:13,815 --> 00:21:17,778
- and kissed their ass !
- [ Boys Laughing ]

272
00:21:33,794 --> 00:21:36,755
Come on.
Come on.

273
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:44,096
One more !
One more, come on !

274
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:50,811
[ Whistling, Cheering ]

275
00:21:55,148 --> 00:21:56,775
Aah !

276
00:22:03,532 --> 00:22:05,325
Fuck you !

277
00:22:12,165 --> 00:22:16,170
[ Trask ]
Mr. Simms, Mr. Willis.

278
00:22:16,253 --> 00:22:18,714
Hmm.

279
00:22:18,797 --> 00:22:23,010
Mrs. Hunsaker says that you gentlemen
were at a vantage point last night...

280
00:22:23,093 --> 00:22:26,680
to observe who was
responsible for this, uh,

281
00:22:26,763 --> 00:22:29,308
stunt.

282
00:22:33,562 --> 00:22:36,648
Who was it ?

283
00:22:36,732 --> 00:22:39,818
I really couldn't
tell you, sir.

284
00:22:39,902 --> 00:22:44,156
Um, I thought I saw someone
fooling with the lamppost,

285
00:22:44,198 --> 00:22:48,660
but by the time I pulled focus,
they were gone.

286
00:22:48,702 --> 00:22:52,497
Mr. Simms ?

287
00:22:52,581 --> 00:22:54,499
I couldn't say.

288
00:22:56,543 --> 00:23:00,547
That automobile is not
just a possession of mine.

289
00:23:00,631 --> 00:23:05,427
That automobile was presented
to me by the Board of Trustees.

290
00:23:05,511 --> 00:23:10,724
It is a symbol of the standard
of excellence for which
this school is known,

291
00:23:10,807 --> 00:23:13,810
and I will not
have it tarnished.

292
00:23:13,894 --> 00:23:15,854
The automobile ?

293
00:23:17,814 --> 00:23:19,942
The standard,
Mr. Willis.

294
00:23:23,487 --> 00:23:27,699
- What's your position, Mr. Simms ?
- On what, sir ?

295
00:23:27,741 --> 00:23:30,035
On preserving the
reputation of Baird.

296
00:23:30,077 --> 00:23:33,956
- I-I'm for Baird.
- Then, who did it ?

297
00:23:35,582 --> 00:23:37,918
I really couldn't say for sure.

298
00:23:43,423 --> 00:23:45,384
Very well.

299
00:23:52,266 --> 00:23:54,685
First thing Monday,
I'm convening a special session...

300
00:23:54,768 --> 00:23:57,229
of the student-faculty
disciplinary committee.

301
00:23:57,271 --> 00:23:59,857
As this is a matter which
concerns the whole school,

302
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,901
the entire student body
will be present.

303
00:24:02,943 --> 00:24:05,612
There will be no classes,
no activities.

304
00:24:05,696 --> 00:24:07,823
Nothing will transpire
at this institution...

305
00:24:07,906 --> 00:24:10,826
until that proceeding
is concluded.

306
00:24:13,036 --> 00:24:17,040
And if, at that time,
we are no further along than we are now,

307
00:24:18,625 --> 00:24:21,795
I will expel you both.

308
00:24:21,879 --> 00:24:24,882
[ Clearing Throat ]

309
00:24:25,883 --> 00:24:28,886
Mr. Willis,
would you excuse us ?

310
00:24:32,097 --> 00:24:35,809
Have a nice Thanksgiving.

311
00:24:35,893 --> 00:24:37,853
Thank you.
You too, Mr. Willis.

312
00:24:37,936 --> 00:24:39,855
I will.

313
00:24:44,651 --> 00:24:46,987
[ Door Closing ]

314
00:24:47,029 --> 00:24:49,323
Mr. Simms.

315
00:24:49,364 --> 00:24:53,118
I'm not quite through
with you yet.

316
00:25:01,835 --> 00:25:05,255
One of the few perks
of this office is that...

317
00:25:05,339 --> 00:25:10,677
I am empowered to handle
certain matters on my own as I see fit.

318
00:25:10,719 --> 00:25:12,679
Do you understand ?

319
00:25:12,721 --> 00:25:15,265
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

320
00:25:15,349 --> 00:25:18,477
The Dean of Admissions at Harvard
and I have an arrangement.

321
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:21,855
Along with the usual sheaf of applicants
submitted by Baird,

322
00:25:21,897 --> 00:25:23,982
of which virtually,

323
00:25:24,024 --> 00:25:27,653
oh, two-thirds are
guaranteed admittance,

324
00:25:27,694 --> 00:25:31,156
I add one name,

325
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:35,202
somebody who's a standout
and yet, underprivileged;

326
00:25:35,285 --> 00:25:41,124
a student who cannot afford to pay
the board and tuition in Cambridge.

327
00:25:43,001 --> 00:25:46,672
Do you know on whose behalf
I drafted a memo this year ?

328
00:25:46,755 --> 00:25:52,219
- No, sir.
- You. You, Mr. Simms.

329
00:25:55,514 --> 00:25:57,724
Now can you tell me
who did it ?

330
00:26:00,269 --> 00:26:02,187
No, sir, I can't.

331
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:06,275
You take the weekend
to think about it, Mr. Simms.

332
00:26:08,652 --> 00:26:11,780
Good afternoon.

333
00:26:13,198 --> 00:26:15,492
What'd he say ?

334
00:26:15,576 --> 00:26:17,744
- Nothin'.
- What do you mean, nothing ?

335
00:26:17,828 --> 00:26:20,163
He said the same thing.
He just said it over.

336
00:26:20,247 --> 00:26:22,291
You know what
he's doing ?

337
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:25,586
He's good-cop,
bad-coppin' us.

338
00:26:25,627 --> 00:26:27,880
He knows I'm old guard.
You're fringe.

339
00:26:27,921 --> 00:26:31,466
He's gonna bear down on me
and soft-soap you.

340
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:36,263
[ Laughing ]
Did he try to soft-soap you ? Did he ?

341
00:26:36,346 --> 00:26:38,891
No.

342
00:26:38,974 --> 00:26:42,060
Chas, I detect a slight panic pulse
from you. Are you panicking ?

343
00:26:42,102 --> 00:26:44,563
- Yeah, a little.
- Come on.

344
00:26:44,605 --> 00:26:47,983
- You're on scholarship, right ?
- Yeah.

345
00:26:48,066 --> 00:26:52,696
You're on scholarship
from Oregon... at Baird.

346
00:26:52,779 --> 00:26:55,741
You're a long way from home, Chas.

347
00:26:55,782 --> 00:26:58,118
What's that got to do
with anything ?

348
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,454
I don't know how
it works out there.

349
00:27:00,537 --> 00:27:04,082
But how it works here ?
We stick together.

350
00:27:04,124 --> 00:27:06,585
It's us against them,
no matter what.

351
00:27:06,627 --> 00:27:10,589
We don't cover our ass.
We don't tell our parents.

352
00:27:10,672 --> 00:27:13,383
Stonewall everybody !

353
00:27:13,467 --> 00:27:18,096
And above all,
never, never...

354
00:27:18,138 --> 00:27:21,808
Leave any of us
twisting in the wind.

355
00:27:22,976 --> 00:27:24,895
And that's it.

356
00:27:24,978 --> 00:27:27,397
What does that have to do
with me being on scholarship ?

357
00:27:27,481 --> 00:27:29,775
Hey, hey !

358
00:27:29,816 --> 00:27:33,320
I'm just tryin' to bring you
up to speed, kid, that's it.

359
00:27:33,403 --> 00:27:36,156
Thanks.

360
00:27:37,699 --> 00:27:42,037
I'll tell you what. Give me a few hours
to figure out the moves,

361
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:45,541
and call me tonight
in Vermont.

362
00:27:45,624 --> 00:27:48,877
I'll be at the Sugarbush lodge,
all right ?

363
00:27:48,961 --> 00:27:51,547
All right.

364
00:27:51,630 --> 00:27:54,091
You all right ?

365
00:27:54,174 --> 00:27:57,135
Yeah, I guess so.

366
00:27:57,177 --> 00:27:59,763
Okay.

367
00:28:01,181 --> 00:28:03,433
Try to keep him down
to four drinks a day.

368
00:28:03,517 --> 00:28:06,353
If you can keep him down to forty,
you're doin' good.

369
00:28:06,436 --> 00:28:09,940
Try to water them down a little.
Do you know how to do that ?

370
00:28:10,023 --> 00:28:14,528
- It's a long ride, honey !
- Get the bags in the car.
I'll be right out.

371
00:28:14,611 --> 00:28:18,907
Mommy, Mommy !
Don't forget Uncle Frank's walk.

372
00:28:18,991 --> 00:28:21,076
[ Mrs. Rossi ]
Oh, ha... Yeah.

373
00:28:21,159 --> 00:28:24,830
Uh, you have to
air him out...

374
00:28:24,872 --> 00:28:27,207
a little every day.

375
00:28:27,291 --> 00:28:30,460
Why don't you go on back there,
get yourself oriented ?

376
00:28:30,544 --> 00:28:35,132
I'll come out in a minute,
give you telephone numbers and stuff.

377
00:28:35,215 --> 00:28:37,759
[ Frank ] Well, I wouldn't try
a thing like that...

378
00:28:37,843 --> 00:28:40,304
unless I knew,
would I ?

379
00:28:40,387 --> 00:28:42,306
Just let me
speak to her.

380
00:28:42,389 --> 00:28:44,308
Hello, beautiful.
Is that you ?

381
00:28:44,391 --> 00:28:47,436
Yeah,
we spoke yesterday.

382
00:28:47,519 --> 00:28:50,355
[ Chuckling ] You have a glass of wine
with lunch ?

383
00:28:50,397 --> 00:28:53,984
You sound
a little dusky. Hmm.

384
00:28:54,067 --> 00:28:57,946
- [ Clearing Throat ]
- Just a minute, sweetheart.

385
00:28:58,030 --> 00:29:01,575
You're back, huh ?

386
00:29:01,658 --> 00:29:03,202
Tenacious !

387
00:29:03,243 --> 00:29:06,663
Get out my dress blues.
They're in a garment bag in the closet.

388
00:29:06,747 --> 00:29:08,790
Check the top dresser drawer.
Take out the shoulder boards...

389
00:29:08,874 --> 00:29:10,918
and affix them
shoulders right and left,

390
00:29:11,001 --> 00:29:13,545
A.S.A.P.
That means now.

391
00:29:13,629 --> 00:29:15,589
Hello.

392
00:29:15,631 --> 00:29:18,926
Sorry to keep you
waitin', sweetheart.

393
00:29:18,967 --> 00:29:21,470
I'm not the kind of guy
who likes to rush things,

394
00:29:21,553 --> 00:29:27,267
but I'm catchin' a 4:00
at Logan, lookin' out my window,
and there's not a taxi in sight.

395
00:29:27,351 --> 00:29:29,686
What happened to Chet ?

396
00:29:29,770 --> 00:29:31,813
He didn't invest
in a radio yet ?

397
00:29:31,897 --> 00:29:35,108
Hah ! Well,
get your driver on it.

398
00:29:35,192 --> 00:29:38,820
Tell him to get
a move on.

399
00:29:38,904 --> 00:29:41,698
Yes. Mmm.

400
00:29:41,782 --> 00:29:46,036
Some kind of body has got to go
with that bedroom voice.

401
00:29:46,119 --> 00:29:48,580
One day I'm gonna swing by,
get a better look at it.

402
00:29:48,664 --> 00:29:51,333
You bet.

403
00:29:51,416 --> 00:29:53,335
Bye.

404
00:29:56,296 --> 00:29:59,842
My val-pak's underneath the bed.
Get it out.

405
00:29:59,925 --> 00:30:01,927
Put the boards on the blues
and fold 'em in.

406
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:05,597
Uh, are we going someplace,
Colonel ?

407
00:30:05,681 --> 00:30:09,059
What business is that of yours ?
Don't shrug, imbecile.

408
00:30:09,142 --> 00:30:14,106
I'm blind. Save your body language
for the bimbi.

409
00:30:14,147 --> 00:30:19,027
- Now, get my gear out.
- Francine, get in the car.

410
00:30:19,111 --> 00:30:23,407
It's almost 3:00. The goddamn
Flintstones haven't left yet.

411
00:30:23,490 --> 00:30:28,537
[ Mr. Rossi ] Willie Rossi
must go in the car !

412
00:30:28,620 --> 00:30:32,332
- Here comes Mrs. Rossi now.
- Damn it !

413
00:30:32,416 --> 00:30:35,794
She said good-bye to me
three times today.

414
00:30:35,836 --> 00:30:38,005
What's she got,
separation anxiety ?

415
00:30:38,088 --> 00:30:41,091
Cut her off
at the door !

416
00:30:42,509 --> 00:30:45,137
Hi, honey.
Bye, honey.

417
00:30:47,723 --> 00:30:50,142
I wish you were
coming with us.

418
00:30:50,225 --> 00:30:52,477
Me too.

419
00:30:52,561 --> 00:30:55,189
Maybe next time.

420
00:30:58,817 --> 00:31:01,361
- Drive carefully now.
- Yeah.

421
00:31:03,572 --> 00:31:06,825
Charlie, this is
where we'll be.

422
00:31:06,867 --> 00:31:09,578
Good luck, Charlie.
Don't let him drink too much.

423
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:16,084
See ya, Charlie !

424
00:31:16,168 --> 00:31:19,838
And no 900 numbers.
He loves to talk dirty.

425
00:31:26,845 --> 00:31:29,765
All right,
let's get to work.

426
00:31:38,732 --> 00:31:41,360
L-buckles
givin' you trouble ?

427
00:31:42,736 --> 00:31:45,030
Never in the Boy Scouts,
sluggo ?

428
00:31:45,072 --> 00:31:48,700
- I, I made Tenderfoot.
- Tenderfoot, my foot !

429
00:31:48,784 --> 00:31:51,078
Convenience-store
mama's boy.

430
00:31:51,161 --> 00:31:53,330
Here. Let me
take a look at that.

431
00:31:53,372 --> 00:31:57,292
Touch me again, I'll kill ya,
you little son-of-a-bitch !

432
00:31:59,211 --> 00:32:03,715
I touch you.
Understand ?

433
00:32:05,926 --> 00:32:10,013
My shoulder boards are in
the top dresser drawer. Get them, son.

434
00:32:10,055 --> 00:32:14,268
The epaulets with
the silver oak leaf.

435
00:32:30,409 --> 00:32:33,370
- Are these --
- Good.

436
00:32:33,412 --> 00:32:35,914
Taxi come yet ?

437
00:32:35,998 --> 00:32:38,375
Colonel,
where are we going ?

438
00:32:38,417 --> 00:32:40,377
Where we going ?

439
00:32:40,419 --> 00:32:42,880
Freak show central.

440
00:32:42,921 --> 00:32:45,757
- Where's that ?
- New York City.

441
00:32:47,634 --> 00:32:50,179
That's in New York, son.
New York State.

442
00:32:50,262 --> 00:32:54,600
Uh, Mrs. Rossi didn't say anything to me
about going anywhere.

443
00:32:54,641 --> 00:32:56,810
She forgot.

444
00:32:56,894 --> 00:32:59,938
- Should we call her, 'cause I --
- You kidding me ?

445
00:33:00,022 --> 00:33:03,817
Call her ? By the time they get to
Albany in that "hupmobile" he drives...

446
00:33:03,901 --> 00:33:06,612
it'll be opening day
at Saratoga.

447
00:33:06,695 --> 00:33:10,699
- Colonel, I can't go to New York City.
- Why not ?

448
00:33:10,782 --> 00:33:12,784
New York --

449
00:33:12,868 --> 00:33:16,538
- New York's too much responsibility.
- Ah, responsibility !

450
00:33:16,622 --> 00:33:19,333
I had a lot of 17 year olds
my first platoon.

451
00:33:19,416 --> 00:33:22,753
I took care of them.
All set !

452
00:33:24,004 --> 00:33:26,757
How do I look ?

453
00:33:26,798 --> 00:33:29,593
Tickets. Money.

454
00:33:29,635 --> 00:33:31,595
Speech.

455
00:33:31,637 --> 00:33:35,265
Old Washington joke...
from my days with Lyndon.

456
00:33:35,349 --> 00:33:39,269
-[ Honking ]
-I knew I could count on transportation.

457
00:33:39,311 --> 00:33:42,189
Are you ready ?

458
00:33:43,398 --> 00:33:46,818
This is not Panmunjom.
A simple yes will do.

459
00:33:46,860 --> 00:33:48,946
- Um --
- Good ! Here you go.

460
00:33:48,987 --> 00:33:51,865
Come on !
Hup to it, son !

461
00:33:51,949 --> 00:33:54,576
You're in front of me.
Let's go.

462
00:33:54,660 --> 00:33:58,121
- [ Meowing ]
- [ Frank ] Tomster, come here, boy.

463
00:33:58,163 --> 00:34:00,749
Psst, psst.
Come on.

464
00:34:00,832 --> 00:34:04,837
Here, tomster, come on.
Tomster, tomster. Yeah.

465
00:34:06,171 --> 00:34:11,134
Remember, when in doubt... fuck.

466
00:34:14,221 --> 00:34:16,807
Good afternoon, sir.
Where's our destination ?

467
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,810
Our destination... New York City,
home of the brave !

468
00:34:19,852 --> 00:34:22,980
- Two for the shuttle to New York.
- I'm not shuttling anywhere.

469
00:34:23,063 --> 00:34:26,859
- Look at those tickets. "First class."
- Yes, sir, first class.

470
00:34:26,942 --> 00:34:30,737
You bought me a ticket ?
I never said I'd go to New York.

471
00:34:30,821 --> 00:34:34,992
What are you, some kind of chicken-shit,
sticks to job description only ?

472
00:34:35,033 --> 00:34:36,994
Gate 46, sir.

473
00:34:37,035 --> 00:34:39,872
- As you were, son.
- Thank you, sir.

474
00:34:39,955 --> 00:34:42,499
Which way's the door ?

475
00:34:42,541 --> 00:34:46,628
- Are you blind ? Are you blind ?
- Of course not.

476
00:34:46,712 --> 00:34:49,965
Then why do you keep grabbin'
my goddamn arm ?

477
00:34:50,048 --> 00:34:53,427
