724
00:50:30,906 --> 00:50:33,325
Nothing.

725
00:50:33,408 --> 00:50:38,539
Next time...
snap it out !

726
00:50:38,622 --> 00:50:44,086
Thumb to palm, index finger
through little digit, smartly aligned,

727
00:50:44,127 --> 00:50:46,713
sharp to the hairline,
down !

728
00:50:51,426 --> 00:50:53,762
Too many men,
far better than you,

729
00:50:53,804 --> 00:50:56,515
have executed
that courtesy.

730
00:50:56,598 --> 00:51:00,143
And if you're smart,
you won't try it again.

731
00:51:03,605 --> 00:51:08,652
This bat has got sharper radar
than the Nautilus.

732
00:51:08,735 --> 00:51:11,196
Don't fuck with me,
Charlie.

733
00:51:21,707 --> 00:51:24,209
See you get
a good night's sleep, son.

734
00:51:33,552 --> 00:51:36,597
[ Groaning ]

735
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:39,308
[ Frank ]
§ It's a lovely day today §

736
00:51:39,391 --> 00:51:42,352
§ So, whatever
you gotta do §

737
00:51:42,436 --> 00:51:45,355
§ You got a lovely day
to do it in that's true §

738
00:51:51,653 --> 00:51:53,655
Good morning, Charlie.

739
00:51:56,491 --> 00:52:00,120
- [ Sigh ] Good morning.
- This is Sofia, Charlie.

740
00:52:00,204 --> 00:52:02,706
She's a magician
with a needle.

741
00:52:02,789 --> 00:52:05,751
Sofia's workin' me up
a little "Glen Plaid" number,

742
00:52:05,834 --> 00:52:08,504
and I've asked her if she'd
put something together for you.

743
00:52:08,587 --> 00:52:12,174
- Uh, I don't need any clothes, Colonel.
- Standard issue...

744
00:52:12,257 --> 00:52:14,843
for an upscale
urban assignment.

745
00:52:14,927 --> 00:52:17,596
You don't like the clothes,
Charlie, on completion of duty,

746
00:52:17,638 --> 00:52:19,848
you can give 'em away.

747
00:52:19,932 --> 00:52:23,268
Juice, coffee, and other assorted
goodies on the trolley over there.

748
00:52:23,310 --> 00:52:25,562
Get yourself up,
get yourself together !

749
00:52:25,646 --> 00:52:29,107
§ It's a great day
for singin' a song §

750
00:52:29,191 --> 00:52:33,111
§ And it's a great day
for movin' along §

751
00:52:33,153 --> 00:52:35,739
§ And it's a great day
from morning to night §

752
00:52:35,822 --> 00:52:39,284
§ And it's
a great day §

753
00:52:39,368 --> 00:52:42,538
for everybody's plight.

754
00:52:42,621 --> 00:52:45,332
[ Frank Chuckling ]

755
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:49,169
How are you feeling
today, Colonel ?

756
00:52:49,253 --> 00:52:52,506
Super !
Superior !

757
00:52:52,589 --> 00:52:55,384
Superfluous !

758
00:52:55,467 --> 00:52:57,594
Young Sofie here
is working Thanksgiving...

759
00:52:57,678 --> 00:52:59,888
because she's trying to
put herself through college.

760
00:52:59,972 --> 00:53:03,475
I told her, "My young friend
Charlie's headed for college."

761
00:53:03,517 --> 00:53:06,144
- Uh, excuse me.
- Where you goin' ?

762
00:53:06,228 --> 00:53:09,857
- I-l need to use the phone.
- What's wrong with the phones in here ?

763
00:53:09,940 --> 00:53:12,484
I don't want
to disturb you.

764
00:53:12,568 --> 00:53:14,611
You're not disturbing me.
Make your call.

765
00:53:14,695 --> 00:53:16,864
I'd kinda like
to be private.

766
00:53:16,947 --> 00:53:19,908
Stay outta my room !

767
00:53:19,992 --> 00:53:22,703
This is as private
as you're gonna get.

768
00:53:25,372 --> 00:53:30,085
§ But if you've got somethin'
that must be done §

769
00:53:30,169 --> 00:53:34,256
§ And it can only
be done by one §

770
00:53:35,340 --> 00:53:38,093
Sofia...

771
00:53:38,177 --> 00:53:41,680
what are the chances
of suitin' you up sometime ?

772
00:53:41,763 --> 00:53:44,725
- [ Operator ] Sugarbush Lodge.
- George Willis, please.

773
00:53:47,728 --> 00:53:51,148
- [ George ] Hello !
- George ! Hey, it's Charlie.

774
00:53:51,231 --> 00:53:54,359
Hey, Chas. Next year you gotta
come up with us.

775
00:53:54,443 --> 00:53:59,531
White powder on
a base of snow bunnies.

776
00:53:59,573 --> 00:54:02,242
Chas,
are you there ?

777
00:54:02,326 --> 00:54:04,536
Yeah, I'm here.
Um --

778
00:54:04,578 --> 00:54:07,706
- you told me to call you for the moves.
- All right.

779
00:54:07,789 --> 00:54:10,584
For now, the move's
no move: status quo.

780
00:54:10,667 --> 00:54:12,586
Everything's
the way we left it.

781
00:54:12,669 --> 00:54:15,255
How did we leave it ?

782
00:54:15,339 --> 00:54:19,009
See no evil,
hear no evil.

783
00:54:19,092 --> 00:54:22,638
You know
what I mean, Chas ?

784
00:54:22,721 --> 00:54:25,599
Yeah. See no evil,
hear no evil.

785
00:54:27,851 --> 00:54:33,065
- Okay, then, walk like you talk !
- All right, good-bye.

786
00:54:33,148 --> 00:54:38,195
- George Willis, huh ?
- Yeah.

787
00:54:38,278 --> 00:54:40,197
George Willis.

788
00:54:40,280 --> 00:54:44,201
That makes his father probably
George Willis, Senior.

789
00:54:44,284 --> 00:54:46,203
Charlie, I ask ya,

790
00:54:46,286 --> 00:54:50,165
what do you think Big George
is gonna feel about Little George...

791
00:54:50,249 --> 00:54:53,293
seeing no evil,
hearing no evil ?

792
00:54:55,879 --> 00:54:58,006
Well, we're not gonna
tell our parents.

793
00:54:58,090 --> 00:55:00,968
We're just gonna keep it
between ourselves.

794
00:55:01,051 --> 00:55:05,222
Oh, George isn't gonna tell
his father about this thing !

795
00:55:05,305 --> 00:55:08,141
Damn decent of him.
Ooh ! Aw ! Hah !

796
00:55:08,225 --> 00:55:10,519
- Scusi.
- Prego.

797
00:55:10,602 --> 00:55:12,980
I love it
when you hurt me.

798
00:55:13,063 --> 00:55:15,524
Uh, tell me now,
Charlie.

799
00:55:15,607 --> 00:55:19,570
This, uh, George Willis, Junior,
what's his father do ?

800
00:55:19,653 --> 00:55:21,697
I don't really know.

801
00:55:21,780 --> 00:55:24,324
Well, I'm gonna tell ya.

802
00:55:24,408 --> 00:55:29,162
When George Willis, Sr., isn't busy as a
million-dollar man for Aetna Casualty --

803
00:55:29,246 --> 00:55:32,666
or is it New England Distributor
for the Chrysler Corporation ?

804
00:55:32,749 --> 00:55:36,753
He concerns himself with his young son,
George Willis, Junior.

805
00:55:36,837 --> 00:55:40,174
George isn't going
to say anything to his father.

806
00:55:40,215 --> 00:55:42,509
Oh, Charlie.

807
00:55:42,551 --> 00:55:44,761
Big George is gonna
wind up Little George,

808
00:55:44,845 --> 00:55:47,973
and Little George is gonna sing
like a canary.

809
00:55:48,015 --> 00:55:50,559
And if you're hip, kid,
you're gonna hop to, too.

810
00:55:50,642 --> 00:55:52,728
You've got this
all figured out, don't you ?

811
00:55:52,811 --> 00:55:57,191
It don't take no Young America merit
scholarship to figure this one out.

812
00:55:57,274 --> 00:56:01,153
Charlie, you had a little life,
so you decided to go to Baird...

813
00:56:01,195 --> 00:56:04,281
to put yourself in the market
for a big one.

814
00:56:04,364 --> 00:56:06,325
Now, in order to stay
in the running,

815
00:56:06,366 --> 00:56:09,244
you're gonna have to tell these people
what they want to know.

816
00:56:09,328 --> 00:56:11,496
You think so ?

817
00:56:11,580 --> 00:56:13,540
- Are we finished, Sofia ?
- Yes.

818
00:56:13,582 --> 00:56:16,460
Grazie. Grazie.

819
00:56:18,253 --> 00:56:20,839
Charlie,

820
00:56:20,881 --> 00:56:23,759
if you don't sing now,

821
00:56:23,842 --> 00:56:27,137
you're gonna end up,
not only shelving biscuits...

822
00:56:27,221 --> 00:56:30,182
in some convenience store
in the Oregon burbs,

823
00:56:30,265 --> 00:56:34,478
probably the last word you'll ever hear
yourself say just before you croak...

824
00:56:34,561 --> 00:56:38,524
gonna be, "Have a nice day
and come back soon."

825
00:56:38,607 --> 00:56:40,776
Sofia !

826
00:56:40,859 --> 00:56:44,821
Measure up Charlie, pronto.
We got a date for Thanksgiving.

827
00:56:44,905 --> 00:56:46,907
We got a date ?

828
00:56:46,990 --> 00:56:49,159
My brother's place.

829
00:56:49,243 --> 00:56:51,995
W.R. Slade,
White Plains, New York.

830
00:56:52,079 --> 00:56:55,541
Colonel, I can't go with you
to your brother's place.

831
00:56:55,582 --> 00:56:58,377
I mean, I should be
getting back to school.

832
00:57:00,754 --> 00:57:05,217
Uh, well you gotta have
Thanksgiving somewhere.

833
00:57:05,300 --> 00:57:09,096
I mean, eats and treats.
I could use the company.

834
00:57:12,724 --> 00:57:15,644
All right.
D-Does he know I'm comin' ?

835
00:57:15,727 --> 00:57:18,647
He doesn't know I'm comin'. But wait
till you see the look on his face...

836
00:57:18,730 --> 00:57:20,649
when I walk through
the door.

837
00:57:20,732 --> 00:57:23,402
Oh, he loves me !

838
00:57:24,736 --> 00:57:28,615
Oh, uh, Charlie,
about your little problem,

839
00:57:28,699 --> 00:57:31,201
there are two kinds of people
in this world:

840
00:57:31,285 --> 00:57:33,704
those who stand up
and face the music,

841
00:57:33,787 --> 00:57:35,706
and those who
run for cover.

842
00:57:35,789 --> 00:57:39,376
Cover's better.
Okay, Sofia, suit 'im up !

843
00:57:39,459 --> 00:57:43,088
Make him pretty !

844
00:57:57,436 --> 00:58:00,397
Careful.

845
00:58:00,439 --> 00:58:03,358
- Should I ring it ?
- Yeah.

846
00:58:09,907 --> 00:58:11,909
Yes ?

847
00:58:11,992 --> 00:58:14,453
Yes !
Who is this ?

848
00:58:14,536 --> 00:58:18,916
- It's Randy.
- Randy ? You new ?

849
00:58:18,957 --> 00:58:21,126
I'm your nephew.

850
00:58:21,210 --> 00:58:23,879
Hah !
Here I am !

851
00:58:23,962 --> 00:58:27,132
Your sister's been
hoarding me long enough.

852
00:58:27,216 --> 00:58:30,135
- Thought it's time to spread
the riches around.
- Uncle Frank !

853
00:58:30,219 --> 00:58:32,179
- Gloria !
- Gail.

854
00:58:32,262 --> 00:58:34,181
Of course.

855
00:58:34,264 --> 00:58:37,726
Say hello to the potluck
party from New York City.

856
00:58:37,809 --> 00:58:40,854
Good old Uncle Frank and this here
with him is Charlie Simms,

857
00:58:40,938 --> 00:58:43,232
star halfback of the
Baird football team.

858
00:58:43,273 --> 00:58:47,528
They not only beat Exeter and Groton,
but Aquinas High School too.

859
00:58:47,611 --> 00:58:50,113
Where's your
miserable father ?

860
00:58:50,197 --> 00:58:52,741
Wait ! No, no.
Let's surprise him.

861
00:58:52,783 --> 00:58:55,869
Give that fat heart
of his an attack. Willie !

862
00:58:58,163 --> 00:59:01,041
Oh, Willie !

863
00:59:11,385 --> 00:59:13,387
Hello, Frank.

864
00:59:13,470 --> 00:59:16,849
- How you doin' ?
- Okay.

865
00:59:16,932 --> 00:59:21,728
Here's my hand.
Charlie, meet W.R. Slade.

866
00:59:21,812 --> 00:59:23,856
Nice to meet you, sir.

867
00:59:23,939 --> 00:59:26,817
The original bulging
briefcase man.

868
00:59:26,900 --> 00:59:31,321
Gretchen, I smell those prunes !
We talkin' Turkey Marbella ?

869
00:59:31,363 --> 00:59:34,116
- Yes, we are.
- Whoo !

870
00:59:34,199 --> 00:59:36,869
Let's have a whiff.
Come on.

871
00:59:36,952 --> 00:59:38,912
You know, I always had a sneaker
for you. Come here.

872
00:59:38,996 --> 00:59:41,123
[ Sniffing ]
Mmm.

873
00:59:41,206 --> 00:59:43,166
Hah !

874
00:59:43,208 --> 00:59:47,462
- Where are you, Garry ?
I heard you cough.
- Who are you again ?

875
00:59:47,504 --> 00:59:52,134
I'm just here at the Waldorf-Astoria
with -- Is it your brother ?

876
00:59:52,217 --> 00:59:54,678
W.R.'s final issue.
How ya doin' ?

877
00:59:54,720 --> 00:59:59,808
- Yes. Who the hell are you ?
- I'm kinda takin' care
of him for the weekend.

878
00:59:59,892 --> 01:00:01,018
Charlie !

879
01:00:01,101 --> 01:00:03,312
Jesus !

880
01:00:03,353 --> 01:00:07,900
Sorry. Where's the booze ?
Flowin' like mud here.

881
01:00:07,983 --> 01:00:12,237
To tell the truth, the colonel's
not well, I don't think.

882
01:00:12,321 --> 01:00:15,407
- Not well ?
- I think he's a little lonely.

883
01:00:15,490 --> 01:00:18,368
Why didn't you take him
to your family's for dinner ?

884
01:00:18,452 --> 01:00:21,079
I heard that !

885
01:00:21,163 --> 01:00:23,540
I heard that.

886
01:00:23,624 --> 01:00:26,251
Pay no attention to him.
That's his big-brother talk.

887
01:00:26,335 --> 01:00:29,004
He's been watching out for me
since day one.

888
01:00:29,046 --> 01:00:33,592
Bailed me out of more trouble...
than he'd like to remember.

889
01:00:33,675 --> 01:00:36,178
- Hmm ?
- [ Gretchen ] Let me take your coat.

890
01:00:36,261 --> 01:00:40,724
I meant to pick up some vino
on my way, but I blew it.

891
01:00:40,807 --> 01:00:43,268
I'll send you the Rothschild
again for Christmas,

892
01:00:43,352 --> 01:00:47,272
- only let's see how Thanksgiving goes.
- I'll set two more places.

893
01:00:47,356 --> 01:00:50,692
- Here's your drink, Frank.
- Thank you, Randy.

894
01:00:50,734 --> 01:00:53,362
Still with
Snow Queen sugar ?

895
01:00:53,403 --> 01:00:57,241
Snow Flake. Why do you
always get that wrong ?

896
01:00:57,324 --> 01:01:00,619
Because it's not important for me to
get it right. What are you doing there ?

897
01:01:00,702 --> 01:01:03,956
I'm Vice President
for Marketing.

898
01:01:04,039 --> 01:01:08,001
Whoo-ah ! Congratulations !
Sugar is shit, though.

899
01:01:08,085 --> 01:01:11,505
I told General Abrams to install
honey in the commissaries.

900
01:01:11,588 --> 01:01:14,883
If the K-50s didn't blow your brains
out, sugar, sure as shit, was gonna.

901
01:01:16,468 --> 01:01:18,804
- Why don't we all sit down ?
- Ooh !

902
01:01:18,887 --> 01:01:22,808
Mitsouki. Rhymes with nookie.
Be careful.

903
01:01:22,891 --> 01:01:26,854
- When the wife gets restless,
the wife gets racy.
- Let's go and eat.

904
01:01:26,937 --> 01:01:31,859
By all means.
Thank you, Charlie.

905
01:01:31,942 --> 01:01:36,071
Where you wanna sit, Frank, or you gonna
arrange yourself at the head again ?

906
01:01:36,154 --> 01:01:40,409
Any old card table
will do. This is fine.

907
01:01:40,492 --> 01:01:43,745
[ Frank ]
Where was I ? Oh !

908
01:01:43,787 --> 01:01:47,207
I wake up. It's four in the morning.
I don't know who I'm with,

909
01:01:47,291 --> 01:01:49,501
why I'm there
and where I am.

910
01:01:49,585 --> 01:01:52,546
What am I gonna do ?
I got this Asian flower,

911
01:01:52,629 --> 01:01:57,092
all giggly and dewy-like;

912
01:01:57,176 --> 01:02:01,054
and this hard-boiled
navy nurse outta Omaha, on the other.

913
01:02:01,138 --> 01:02:05,434
We're three across the bed,
not a stitch of clothes on.

914
01:02:05,475 --> 01:02:07,895
It comes to me.

915
01:02:07,978 --> 01:02:12,566
Let east meet west.
We'll build a golden bridge.

916
01:02:12,649 --> 01:02:14,359
[ Frank ]
Hah-hah !

917
01:02:14,443 --> 01:02:17,112
I felt like I'd just joined
the corps of engineers !

918
01:02:21,992 --> 01:02:24,661
We all still here ?

919
01:02:24,745 --> 01:02:28,165
It's a beautiful story.
[ Cough ]

920
01:02:30,375 --> 01:02:34,963
- Do you always enjoy
shocking people, Uncle Frank ?
- Honey.

921
01:02:35,047 --> 01:02:37,341
I didn't know you were
so easily shocked.

922
01:02:37,424 --> 01:02:39,968
I admire your sensibilities.
I'm touched.

923
01:02:40,052 --> 01:02:43,096
Dad, remember the time
you persuaded Frank...

924
01:02:43,180 --> 01:02:46,517
- to go to the kennel ?
- What about it ?

925
01:02:46,600 --> 01:02:49,895
- He almost put the seeing eye
dog business outta business.
- Cool it, Randy.

926
01:02:49,978 --> 01:02:54,149
- It's over and done with.
- Indeed it is, Garry.

927
01:02:54,233 --> 01:02:56,568
Indeed it is.
So is dinner.

928
01:02:56,652 --> 01:02:59,738
Charlie, what time do you have ?
I think we better be gettin' back.

929
01:02:59,821 --> 01:03:04,743
- You ever given any thought
to a braille watch, Frank ?
- Randy.

930
01:03:04,826 --> 01:03:08,789
- Stevie Wonder wears one,
or do you rank on him too ?
- Honey, please.

931
01:03:08,872 --> 01:03:11,166
It's all right, Gloria.
I enjoy Randy's observations.

932
01:03:11,208 --> 01:03:15,170
My wife's name is Gail, Frank.
Can you hear that ? Gail.

933
01:03:15,254 --> 01:03:17,714
Excuse me.
Gail.

934
01:03:17,798 --> 01:03:21,552
Gail strikes me as
a very beautiful woman,

935
01:03:21,635 --> 01:03:24,221
but there's a
little tension in her voice.

936
01:03:24,304 --> 01:03:27,099
It could be one
of two things:

937
01:03:27,182 --> 01:03:29,560
either Gail is nervous
or unsatisfied.

938
01:03:30,269 --> 01:03:34,106
What's your point,
Uncle Frank ?

939
01:03:34,106 --> 01:03:36,441
You oughta go down
on her.

940
01:03:36,483 --> 01:03:38,610
Cut it out, Frank,
will ya ?

941
01:03:38,694 --> 01:03:42,072
You're so wrapped up in sugar, you've
forgotten the taste of real honey !

942
01:03:42,114 --> 01:03:43,991
Frank,
for God's sake !

943
01:03:44,074 --> 01:03:46,702
Hear that voice ?
There's fire under that dress.

944
01:03:46,785 --> 01:03:48,871
- Will you cut it out ?
- Just get the fuck outta here.

945
01:03:48,954 --> 01:03:51,373
- Whoo-ah !
- Get in your limousine.

946
01:03:51,456 --> 01:03:54,626
Go down to the bowery, get with the
other fucking drunks where you belong !

947
01:03:54,710 --> 01:03:56,879
- Wait a minute.
- What ?

948
01:03:56,962 --> 01:03:59,923
- Could you take it easy ?
- What for ?

949
01:03:59,965 --> 01:04:02,467
You want me to lay off him,
Chuckie, 'cause he's blind ?

950
01:04:02,551 --> 01:04:05,512
- No, but I mean --
- My friend's name is Charles.

951
01:04:05,596 --> 01:04:08,098
He doesn't like
to be called Chuckie.

952
01:04:08,140 --> 01:04:11,810
- This is supposed to be a family
get-together. This is --
- A warning.

953
01:04:11,894 --> 01:04:16,064
Jesus Christ. Another sucker who thinks
this shitheel's a war hero.

