01:22:15,853 --> 01:22:18,146
- Don't pay any attention to him.
- What's your name ?

1196
01:22:18,230 --> 01:22:19,731
Donna.

1197
01:22:19,815 --> 01:22:24,528
- Donna ? I'm Frank. This here is --
- This is Charlie.

1198
01:22:24,611 --> 01:22:26,738
Yes. She likes you.

1199
01:22:26,822 --> 01:22:30,033
Charlie's having a difficult weekend.
He's going through a crisis.

1200
01:22:30,117 --> 01:22:32,870
How does he look
like he's holding up ?

1201
01:22:32,953 --> 01:22:35,914
He looks fine to me.

1202
01:22:35,956 --> 01:22:38,417
Oh ! She does
like you, Charlie.

1203
01:22:43,088 --> 01:22:45,340
So, Donna,

1204
01:22:45,424 --> 01:22:47,134
ah...

1205
01:22:47,217 --> 01:22:49,219
do you tango ?

1206
01:22:49,303 --> 01:22:52,890
No. I wanted
to learn once, but --

1207
01:22:52,973 --> 01:22:55,350
But ?

1208
01:22:55,434 --> 01:22:58,020
But Michael
didn't want to.

1209
01:22:58,103 --> 01:23:01,481
Michael, the one
you're waiting for.

1210
01:23:01,565 --> 01:23:05,277
Michael thinks
the tango's hysterical.

1211
01:23:05,360 --> 01:23:08,614
Well, I think
Michael's hysterical.

1212
01:23:08,697 --> 01:23:11,909
Don't pay any attention to him.
Did I already say that ?

1213
01:23:13,827 --> 01:23:16,330
What a beautiful laugh.

1214
01:23:17,831 --> 01:23:19,833
Thank you, Frank.

1215
01:23:24,588 --> 01:23:27,716
Would you like to learn
to tango, Donna ?

1216
01:23:30,802 --> 01:23:32,804
Right now ?

1217
01:23:32,846 --> 01:23:37,518
I'm offering you my services...
free of charge.

1218
01:23:37,601 --> 01:23:39,561
What do you say ?

1219
01:23:39,645 --> 01:23:41,438
Ah...

1220
01:23:41,522 --> 01:23:44,650
I think I'd be
a little afraid.

1221
01:23:44,733 --> 01:23:46,902
Of what ?

1222
01:23:46,985 --> 01:23:51,240
Afraid of making
a mistake.

1223
01:23:51,323 --> 01:23:55,619
No mistakes in the tango,
not like life.

1224
01:23:55,702 --> 01:23:58,288
It's simple. That's what makes
the tango so great.

1225
01:23:58,372 --> 01:24:03,210
If you make a mistake,
get all tangled up, just tango on.

1226
01:24:03,293 --> 01:24:06,797
[ Frank ]
Why don't you try ?

1227
01:24:10,592 --> 01:24:13,220
Will you try it ?

1228
01:24:13,303 --> 01:24:16,807
All right.
I'll give it a try.

1229
01:24:16,890 --> 01:24:19,560
Hold me down, son.

1230
01:24:26,608 --> 01:24:29,069
Your arm.

1231
01:24:30,863 --> 01:24:33,490
Charlie,

1232
01:24:33,574 --> 01:24:36,118
I'm gonna need some
coordinates here, son.

1233
01:24:36,201 --> 01:24:39,162
The floor's
about 20 by 30,

1234
01:24:39,246 --> 01:24:42,207
And you're at
the long end.

1235
01:24:42,291 --> 01:24:46,295
There's tables on the outside.
The band's on the right.

1236
01:27:25,120 --> 01:27:29,791
Oh, Frank, you are
one incredible dancer.

1237
01:27:32,336 --> 01:27:36,006
Wait'll you see
Charlie dance.

1238
01:27:36,089 --> 01:27:39,218
- He's a liar. I don't dance.
- Isn't he a charmer, though ?

1239
01:27:39,301 --> 01:27:43,472
Truth is, not only can he dance,
but he'll sing you a hell of a tune.

1240
01:27:43,555 --> 01:27:46,225
He can do bird calls
and imitate Bela Lugosi.

1241
01:27:46,308 --> 01:27:48,352
- Hi, honey.
- Hey.

1242
01:27:48,435 --> 01:27:52,064
Michael, this is Frank
and this is Charlie.

1243
01:27:52,147 --> 01:27:55,776
-Hi, Frank, Charlie. I'm sorry I'm late.
-Oh, that's okay.

1244
01:27:55,859 --> 01:27:58,570
These two gentlemen
entertained me,

1245
01:27:58,612 --> 01:28:01,240
and time flew.

1246
01:28:01,323 --> 01:28:05,118
Your girl is...
a hell of a tango dancer.

1247
01:28:05,202 --> 01:28:07,829
You found someone to tango with.
That's terrific !

1248
01:28:07,913 --> 01:28:09,915
Let me
shake your hand.

1249
01:28:09,998 --> 01:28:13,252
- No, it was Frank.
- Hell, I'll shake both your hands !

1250
01:28:14,753 --> 01:28:17,548
Honey, this looks like the place,
but we gotta go.

1251
01:28:17,631 --> 01:28:20,717
We got a date with Darryl
and Carol in the village.

1252
01:28:20,801 --> 01:28:22,719
Do you have a check ?

1253
01:28:22,803 --> 01:28:27,474
- Michael, please. My pleasure.
- No, no. I got this.

1254
01:28:27,558 --> 01:28:30,394
Michael, get your hand outta
your pocket. I'll take it. Really.

1255
01:28:30,477 --> 01:28:33,981
Allow me.

1256
01:28:34,064 --> 01:28:36,608
Why, thank you.

1257
01:28:36,650 --> 01:28:38,652
Bye, guys.

1258
01:28:38,694 --> 01:28:40,863
Bye.

1259
01:28:48,036 --> 01:28:51,874
Darryl and Carol.
Yeah.

1260
01:28:59,840 --> 01:29:03,135
[ Manny ] It's Apartment 17 E, Colonel.
She's expecting you.

1261
01:29:03,218 --> 01:29:07,139
You don't have to worry about a thing.
She's the creme de la creme.

1262
01:29:07,181 --> 01:29:09,683
My buddy took the Vice Chancellor
of Germany to her.

1263
01:29:09,766 --> 01:29:12,186
Now he wants to immigrate
to this country.

1264
01:29:12,269 --> 01:29:14,313
[ Frank ]
You did good, hombre.

1265
01:29:16,690 --> 01:29:19,526
My hair,
how is it ?

1266
01:29:19,568 --> 01:29:21,528
It's perfect.

1267
01:29:24,364 --> 01:29:28,577
- I got the red foulard okay, didn't I ?
- Yeah, real dark red.

1268
01:29:28,660 --> 01:29:31,038
Burgundy, Charlie,
burgundy.

1269
01:29:31,121 --> 01:29:33,999
They love it.

1270
01:29:34,041 --> 01:29:36,668
Bay Rum.

1271
01:29:37,669 --> 01:29:40,714
Windsor knot.

1272
01:29:40,797 --> 01:29:43,675
[ Sigh ] That's my heart
I'm feelin'.

1273
01:29:52,434 --> 01:29:54,436
I'm off.

1274
01:30:12,621 --> 01:30:14,581
Can you get long distance
on this ?

1275
01:30:14,665 --> 01:30:16,667
And how.
Be my guest.

1276
01:30:28,136 --> 01:30:31,014
- Sugarbush lodge.
- Hi. George Willis, please ?

1277
01:30:31,098 --> 01:30:33,684
One moment, please.

1278
01:30:34,476 --> 01:30:36,436
- Hello ?
- Ah, Harry ?

1279
01:30:36,520 --> 01:30:38,772
Chas, how are you ?

1280
01:30:38,856 --> 01:30:42,025
You just caught us. We're about
to shoot George over to the airport.

1281
01:30:42,109 --> 01:30:44,945
Why is George
going to the airport ?

1282
01:30:44,987 --> 01:30:48,365
Um, hold on. Maybe you should talk
to the man himself.

1283
01:30:49,658 --> 01:30:51,702
- Chas.
- Yeah. Hi, George.

1284
01:30:51,785 --> 01:30:55,747
- You just caught me.
- Harry said. Where you goin' ?

1285
01:30:55,831 --> 01:30:58,333
- Home.
- To Boston ?

1286
01:30:58,417 --> 01:31:01,295
Catching the puddle jumper.
Keep your fingers crossed.

1287
01:31:01,378 --> 01:31:04,882
What are you
going home for ?

1288
01:31:04,965 --> 01:31:08,719
[ Sigh ] I was thinking, Chas.
This asshole, Trask ?

1289
01:31:08,802 --> 01:31:11,471
He's making
no sense at all.

1290
01:31:11,555 --> 01:31:15,309
Somebody's gotta talk to him.
My father's Class of '59.

1291
01:31:15,350 --> 01:31:19,188
Your father ? I thought we were
gonna keep our parents outta this.

1292
01:31:19,271 --> 01:31:23,525
This guy Trask is outta control, Chas.
Outta control !

1293
01:31:23,609 --> 01:31:25,903
Somebody's gotta
talk to him.

1294
01:31:25,986 --> 01:31:29,948
- My father's a major
fund-raiser, you know.
- No, I didn't.

1295
01:31:30,032 --> 01:31:33,785
Just relax.
He'll get us off the hook.

1296
01:31:33,869 --> 01:31:36,997
- I gotta go. Everything all right ?
- Sure.

1297
01:31:37,080 --> 01:31:40,959
- I'll see you Monday. Good-bye.
- Bye.

1298
01:32:05,234 --> 01:32:07,694
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

1299
01:32:19,581 --> 01:32:21,542
Hiya, Charlie.

1300
01:32:23,085 --> 01:32:25,087
Watch the door.

1301
01:32:42,980 --> 01:32:45,524
What a beautiful woman.

1302
01:32:58,745 --> 01:33:02,708
- Hello, there.
- Do you see what I see ?

1303
01:33:02,791 --> 01:33:05,919
[ TV ] Yeah.
Either there's something wrong,

1304
01:33:06,003 --> 01:33:08,422
or we got the
world's worst hangover.

1305
01:33:08,505 --> 01:33:12,676
Won't you come in ?

1306
01:33:12,759 --> 01:33:14,720
[ TV Off ]

1307
01:33:30,694 --> 01:33:32,654
Colonel ?

1308
01:33:45,250 --> 01:33:48,545
Colonel,
you all right ?

1309
01:33:48,629 --> 01:33:51,465
What is there ?

1310
01:33:55,052 --> 01:34:00,265
It's afternoon.
You've been sleeping all morning.

1311
01:34:00,349 --> 01:34:02,976
So what ?

1312
01:34:03,060 --> 01:34:06,688
I don't know.
I thought --

1313
01:34:11,068 --> 01:34:13,111
I-l talked to George
last night.

1314
01:34:13,195 --> 01:34:15,405
His, ah --

1315
01:34:15,489 --> 01:34:19,868
His father's a big-deal alumnus
at school. He's got a lot of pull.

1316
01:34:19,952 --> 01:34:22,996
Really ?

1317
01:34:23,080 --> 01:34:26,834
Yeah, he's, ah,

1318
01:34:26,917 --> 01:34:29,211
he's gonna talk
to the headmaster.

1319
01:34:29,294 --> 01:34:32,589
George thinks he might
be able to get us off the hook.

1320
01:34:32,673 --> 01:34:35,342
"Get us off the hook."

1321
01:34:35,425 --> 01:34:38,178
Yeah, that's --
that's what he said.

1322
01:34:38,220 --> 01:34:42,057
Watch the "us" part.

1323
01:34:43,892 --> 01:34:46,728
Colonel, don't you wanna
get up and do something ?

1324
01:34:46,812 --> 01:34:49,773
[ Groan ]

1325
01:34:50,941 --> 01:34:52,776
Colonel ?

1326
01:34:52,860 --> 01:34:56,446
Oh, Charlie,
what do ya want ?

1327
01:34:56,530 --> 01:34:58,490
I don't know !

1328
01:34:58,574 --> 01:35:01,702
But you're
making me nervous.

1329
01:35:04,663 --> 01:35:07,833
My wallet is on
the dresser.

1330
01:35:07,916 --> 01:35:10,127
Take out
your plane ticket...

1331
01:35:10,210 --> 01:35:15,048
and $400
mustering-out pay,

1332
01:35:15,090 --> 01:35:17,509
plus...

1333
01:35:17,593 --> 01:35:21,972
airport-to-school taxi.

1334
01:35:23,432 --> 01:35:26,518
Colonel, it's no rush.
I mean, I can --

1335
01:35:26,602 --> 01:35:28,604
I could stay
for a while.

1336
01:35:28,687 --> 01:35:32,566
Charlie, you already
gave me a day.

1337
01:35:32,608 --> 01:35:36,570
For that day,
I am eternally grateful.

1338
01:35:38,363 --> 01:35:43,076
But right now I have...
other plans.

1339
01:35:43,160 --> 01:35:45,787
What other plans
do you have ?

1340
01:35:47,915 --> 01:35:49,917
To die, son.

1341
01:35:50,000 --> 01:35:54,129
Colonel, you're --

1342
01:35:54,213 --> 01:35:56,924
Come on, Colonel,
you're not gonna die today.

1343
01:35:56,965 --> 01:36:00,761
Charlie,
give me your hand.

1344
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:07,267
You go now, boy.
Okay ?

1345
01:36:09,102 --> 01:36:12,147
You go.
Just, uh --

1346
01:36:14,733 --> 01:36:17,069
Just leave me
sleep here.

1347
01:36:18,153 --> 01:36:21,323
Look, uh --
Can we start over, please ?

1348
01:36:21,406 --> 01:36:25,619
What do you feel
like doin' today, huh ?

1349
01:36:25,702 --> 01:36:28,205
I mean, look at this.
The sun is shining !

1350
01:36:28,288 --> 01:36:30,749
It's a beautiful day.
Let's --

1351
01:36:34,086 --> 01:36:37,589
Colonel, I know you don't want
to be a party poop,

1352
01:36:37,673 --> 01:36:41,677
so let's go out and do something, huh ?
Let's go for a ride.

1353
01:36:46,932 --> 01:36:49,059
Yeah, a ride.

1354
01:36:49,142 --> 01:36:52,354
A ride ?

1355
01:36:52,437 --> 01:36:56,149
Yeah, Colonel Slade,
what do you say ?

1356
01:36:56,233 --> 01:36:59,278
Let's go for a ride,
huh ?

1357
01:37:06,034 --> 01:37:08,370
What kind of ride ?

1358
01:37:09,788 --> 01:37:11,999
Yeah, this is a valid
Oregon driver's license,

1359
01:37:12,541 --> 01:37:16,003
and we let appropriate customers
test-drive the Testarossa.

1360
01:37:16,086 --> 01:37:20,090
But you're 17 and with
a blind companion. That we don't do.

1361
01:37:20,174 --> 01:37:23,093
This is a $190,000
piece of machinery.

1362
01:37:23,177 --> 01:37:26,555
- I'm not letting it out this door.
- How 'bout this one over here ?

1363
01:37:26,638 --> 01:37:29,474
That's a Cabriolet T.
The same deal.

1364
01:37:29,558 --> 01:37:33,854
Think I'm gonna let an unaccompanied kid
get behind the wheel of a $110,000 car ?

1365
01:37:33,937 --> 01:37:36,440
He will not be
unaccompanied.

1366
01:37:36,523 --> 01:37:40,110
I'll be with him.
I'm his father.

1367
01:37:40,194 --> 01:37:43,155
- You're his father ?
- Yes.

1368
01:37:43,238 --> 01:37:46,533
I have an idea. Why don't I take
your father for a test-drive ?

1369
01:37:46,617 --> 01:37:50,537
- What's your quota, Freddie ?
- Don't worry about my quota. I do well.

1370
01:37:50,579 --> 01:37:52,623
How many Ferraris
you sold this month ?

1371
01:37:52,706 --> 01:37:55,375
That's not relevant
to this discussion.

1372
01:37:55,459 --> 01:37:57,544
Freddie,
the 80s are over.

1373
01:37:57,628 --> 01:38:00,339
Are you tryin' to tell me
these are just walkin' outta the store ?

1374
01:38:00,422 --> 01:38:04,593
This is a Ferrari, the finest machinery
made in the automobile industry.

1375
01:38:04,676 --> 01:38:07,554
If you like it that much,
why are you sellin' it ?

1376
01:38:07,638 --> 01:38:12,476
- I'd love to accommodate you --
- If this car performs
the way I expect it to,

1377
01:38:12,559 --> 01:38:18,023
you'll get a certified check of $101,000
and change when in you come tomorrow.

1378
01:38:18,106 --> 01:38:22,653
It's $109,000,
plus $950, plus tax.

1379
01:38:22,736 --> 01:38:25,697
Freddie, for you...

1380
01:38:25,781 --> 01:38:27,950
107 all in,

1381
01:38:28,033 --> 01:38:31,578
plus a case of champagne
to go with your leftover turkey.

1382
01:38:31,662 --> 01:38:35,582
What do you say ?
Don't worry about the boy.

1383
01:38:35,624 --> 01:38:39,253
He drives so smooth,
you can boil an egg on the engine.

1384
01:38:39,336 --> 01:38:42,422
When we bring the car back,
I'll peel the egg for ya.

1385
01:38:42,506 --> 01:38:46,468
Listen, you made me laugh,
but I can't let the car go out.

1386
01:38:48,554 --> 01:38:50,514
Want a deposit ?

1387
01:38:50,597 --> 01:38:53,559
This is not an
installment item, sir.

1388
01:38:56,728 --> 01:39:00,732
Freddie, you're no
spring chicken, are ya ?

1389
01:39:02,442 --> 01:39:06,697
Well, you know what they call me
at the home office ? The gray ghost.

1390
01:39:06,780 --> 01:39:09,116
You know why they
still keep me around ?

1391
01:39:09,157 --> 01:39:12,536
There's no kid here that
can move a Ferrari like I can.

1392
01:39:12,619 --> 01:39:15,497
I'm known from coast to coast
like butter and toast.

1393
01:39:15,581 --> 01:39:17,833
Ask anybody about
Freddie Bisco.

1394
01:39:17,916 --> 01:39:20,836
When I get a Ferrari...
out the door !

1395
01:39:20,919 --> 01:39:24,548
- Hah ! You just made me laugh.
- Yeah ?

1396
01:39:24,631 --> 01:39:28,510
Two thousand.

1397
01:39:28,594 --> 01:39:31,471
Unless you take it,
you're gonna make me cry.

1398
01:39:34,766 --> 01:39:37,811
I'm a gray ghost too.

1399
01:39:47,988 --> 01:39:51,074
See ? This is fun,
isn't it ?

1400
01:40:01,126 --> 01:40:04,087
[ Engine Sputtering ]

1401
01:40:04,171 --> 01:40:07,549
- [ Engine Stops ]
- Drop her into neutral.

1402
01:40:07,633 --> 01:40:10,594
Slide her into second.
Pop the clutch.

1403
01:40:14,556 --> 01:40:17,601
[ Engine Revving ]

1404
01:40:48,715 --> 01:40:52,469
Straight. Hold it
right like that. Feel it ?

1405
01:40:52,511 --> 01:40:56,098
That's straight.
Just keep it straight.

1406
01:40:58,684 --> 01:41:01,687
- Keep it straight.
- No fun just to keep it straight.

1407
01:41:01,770 --> 01:41:05,065
You've got to move a little bit,
feel the road.

1408
01:41:05,148 --> 01:41:08,151
Please ? Just like this.
All right ? There you go.

1409
01:41:08,193 --> 01:41:11,154
[ Charlie ]
Take it nice and easy.

1410
01:41:11,196 --> 01:41:14,241
Do you like this ?

1411
01:41:16,368 --> 01:41:19,705
Slow it down a little.
You goin' a little fast.

1412
01:41:19,788 --> 01:41:23,208
Colonel, slow it down.

1413
01:41:23,292 --> 01:41:25,669
Something's happened
to my foot !

1414
01:41:27,254 --> 01:41:29,214
- Slow it down, please.
- Hold on, Charlie.

1415
01:41:29,298 --> 01:41:31,466
I think I've got
another gear.

1416
01:41:31,550 --> 01:41:33,302
Colonel Slade ?

1417
01:41:35,387 --> 01:41:37,764
- Whoo-ah !
- Oh shit !

1418
01:41:37,848 --> 01:41:40,559
Watch out !

1419
01:41:40,642 --> 01:41:42,603
Hah-hah !

1420
01:41:42,686 --> 01:41:44,897
You'll get us killed !

1421
01:41:44,980 --> 01:41:48,942
Don't blame me, Charlie.
I can't see !

1422
01:41:49,026 --> 01:41:51,987
- Colonel, slow it down !
- [ Laughing ]

1423
01:42:00,078 --> 01:42:02,915
Oh, God.
Oh, Jesus !

1424
01:42:02,956 --> 01:42:05,751
Now let's see
how this baby corners.

1425
01:42:05,834 --> 01:42:08,795
- Corners ?
- Yeah. Say when.

1426
01:42:08,879 --> 01:42:11,507
- Say when what ?
- Say when to turn.

1427
01:42:11,590 --> 01:42:15,052
- Colonel, you can't turn the car.
- Where's the turn, Charlie ?

1428
01:42:15,135 --> 01:42:19,181
3:00 ? 2:00 ?
Right oblique ? Right face ?

1429
01:42:19,264 --> 01:42:20,974
Come on !
Talk to me !

1430
01:42:21,058 --> 01:42:23,435
Ah... it's left, I guess.

1431
01:42:23,519 --> 01:42:26,230
Left. I knew it.
Okay. Now ?

