the Baird tradition.

1773
02:13:43,607 --> 02:13:47,110
And, as the custodians
of that tradition,

1774
02:13:47,194 --> 02:13:52,115
we are here today
to protect each other...

1775
02:13:52,199 --> 02:13:55,827
from those
who threaten it.

1776
02:13:55,911 --> 02:13:58,539
Who is this, Mr. Simms ?

1777
02:13:58,622 --> 02:14:02,626
- Uh --
- This is Mr. Frank Slade,

1778
02:14:02,709 --> 02:14:06,171
Lieutenant Colonel,
United States Army, retired.

1779
02:14:07,381 --> 02:14:09,675
I'm here in place
of Charlie's parents.

1780
02:14:09,758 --> 02:14:13,554
- Excuse me ?
- In loco parentis.

1781
02:14:15,472 --> 02:14:18,392
They could not make
the trip from Oregon today.

1782
02:14:18,433 --> 02:14:20,936
And what is your relationship
to Mr. Simms ?

1783
02:14:21,019 --> 02:14:24,314
Is this a courtroom ?

1784
02:14:24,398 --> 02:14:27,693
- Closest thing we could manage to it.
- Then if we're taking oaths,

1785
02:14:27,776 --> 02:14:30,279
there's a few people
I'd like to swear in.

1786
02:14:32,573 --> 02:14:37,286
There are no oaths at Baird.
We are all on our honor.

1787
02:14:39,746 --> 02:14:42,457
Larry and Franny Simms...

1788
02:14:42,541 --> 02:14:45,460
are very dear,
close friends of mine.

1789
02:14:45,544 --> 02:14:49,548
They've asked me to appear here
on Charlie's behalf.

1790
02:14:49,631 --> 02:14:52,217
Okay ?

1791
02:14:53,468 --> 02:14:55,929
Happy to have you
with us, Colonel.

1792
02:15:00,142 --> 02:15:02,102
Mr. Willis.

1793
02:15:03,937 --> 02:15:07,274
- Which Mr. Willis ?
- George, Junior, sir.

1794
02:15:11,904 --> 02:15:15,240
You were in a position
last Tuesday night...

1795
02:15:15,282 --> 02:15:19,328
to see who committed
this act of vandalism. Who was it ?

1796
02:15:21,705 --> 02:15:24,958
Well, uh, I have
an idea who it was.

1797
02:15:25,042 --> 02:15:28,462
No, no, not an idea, Mr. Willis.
Did you see or did you not see ?

1798
02:15:31,632 --> 02:15:33,550
Well...

1799
02:15:34,635 --> 02:15:37,429
I-l didn't have
my contacts in.

1800
02:15:40,933 --> 02:15:43,101
Come on.

1801
02:15:46,146 --> 02:15:49,107
I was in the library.
I'd taken my glasses off,

1802
02:15:49,191 --> 02:15:52,402
and I was gonna put
my contacts back in.

1803
02:15:52,486 --> 02:15:54,571
Um,

1804
02:15:54,655 --> 02:15:56,865
I --

1805
02:15:56,949 --> 02:15:58,867
Then I helped
Simms close up,

1806
02:15:58,951 --> 02:16:02,454
and the next thing I know,
we're outside,

1807
02:16:02,496 --> 02:16:06,333
and I hear this sound,
and l, um,

1808
02:16:06,416 --> 02:16:09,503
didn't have any time
to put my contacts in.

1809
02:16:09,586 --> 02:16:12,464
Whom, with your limited vision,
did you see ?

1810
02:16:16,927 --> 02:16:19,346
[ Whispering ]

1811
02:16:30,274 --> 02:16:32,693
Like I say,
it was blurry.

1812
02:16:33,861 --> 02:16:35,988
Uh,

1813
02:16:38,115 --> 02:16:40,826
I can't see
without my contacts.

1814
02:16:40,868 --> 02:16:43,245
What did you see,
Mr. Willis ?

1815
02:16:43,328 --> 02:16:45,706
What ?

1816
02:16:45,789 --> 02:16:48,500
- What, you mean definitively ?
- Stop fencing with me, Mr. Willis !

1817
02:16:48,584 --> 02:16:51,545
Tell me what you saw !

1818
02:16:55,591 --> 02:16:58,177
Now, don't hold me
to this, but...

1819
02:16:58,260 --> 02:17:01,054
no contacts, it's dark...

1820
02:17:02,431 --> 02:17:04,391
and everything, I mean --

1821
02:17:04,433 --> 02:17:07,811
- Mr. Willis !
- [ Willis Sighing ]

1822
02:17:07,895 --> 02:17:12,357
Maybe...

1823
02:17:12,441 --> 02:17:15,027
Harry Havemeyer,

1824
02:17:15,068 --> 02:17:18,071
Trent Potter
and Jimmy Jameson.

1825
02:17:22,367 --> 02:17:25,454
- Maybe ?
- Ballpark, best guess.

1826
02:17:27,247 --> 02:17:31,460
[ Trask ] Could you provide us
with some detail ?

1827
02:17:31,543 --> 02:17:33,879
I mean, why don't
you ask Charlie ?

1828
02:17:33,921 --> 02:17:37,216
I really think
he was closer.

1829
02:17:44,932 --> 02:17:46,892
Mr. Simms.

1830
02:17:46,934 --> 02:17:49,228
[ Clearing Throat ]
Yes.

1831
02:17:49,269 --> 02:17:51,480
You don't wear
contact lenses, do you ?

1832
02:17:51,563 --> 02:17:53,941
No, sir.

1833
02:17:55,359 --> 02:17:59,571
With your untrammeled sight,
whom did you see ?

1834
02:18:03,867 --> 02:18:06,036
Well, I saw --
I saw something,

1835
02:18:07,496 --> 02:18:10,499
but l-l-l
I couldn't say who.

1836
02:18:10,582 --> 02:18:13,502
[ Trask ] All right.
What was the something you saw ?

1837
02:18:17,798 --> 02:18:20,592
- I-l couldn't say.
- You couldn't say or you wouldn't say ?

1838
02:18:23,303 --> 02:18:25,264
Well, I just --
I --

1839
02:18:28,976 --> 02:18:31,478
- I just couldn't say. I'm --
- Couldn't, wouldn't, shouldn't.

1840
02:18:31,520 --> 02:18:33,480
You're exhausting
my patience...

1841
02:18:33,522 --> 02:18:35,732
and making a mockery
of these proceedings.

1842
02:18:35,816 --> 02:18:36,942
I will give you
one last chance.

1843
02:18:36,984 --> 02:18:39,570
The consequences of your response
will be dire.

1844
02:18:39,653 --> 02:18:44,992
By dire I mean your future
will be jeopardized permanently.

1845
02:18:45,075 --> 02:18:47,327
Now for the last time,

1846
02:18:47,411 --> 02:18:49,997
what did you see
last Tuesday night...

1847
02:18:50,080 --> 02:18:51,999
outside my office ?

1848
02:18:55,210 --> 02:18:57,171
I saw somebody.

1849
02:18:57,212 --> 02:18:59,923
"l saw somebody." Good.

1850
02:19:01,008 --> 02:19:03,010
Did you see
their size and shape ?

1851
02:19:03,093 --> 02:19:05,888
Yeah.

1852
02:19:05,971 --> 02:19:09,433
And they were
the size and shape of whom ?

1853
02:19:15,063 --> 02:19:18,901
They were
the size and shape --

1854
02:19:32,539 --> 02:19:35,334
of most any
Baird student, sir.

1855
02:19:49,264 --> 02:19:51,892
